<br/><h2 class="text-16 fw-500">11. SECURITY ARRANGEMENTS:</h2>
<p class="text-15 text-dark-1 mt-5">
• Your Luggage shall be weighed at the location and recorded by the images loaded prior to pick up. The images will be available under “Manage Orders”.<br/>
• Each Luggage shall be secured in separate bags/suitcase. The bags are marked and security enabled for easy identification. Each bag will be locked with special security measures so as to prevent any loss of contents. We understand the sensitivity and safety of your Luggage and we undertake all reasonable steps to we ensure the required special care and handling of your Sealed Luggage. The bags are locked and therefore the handles, trolleys and pockets will not be accessible by us. The Sealed Luggage will be opened only on delivery on request. The Sealed Luggage may incur wear and tear during transit due to wheels or other sharp items protruding or present in the Sealed Luggage.
Items that come under the fragile category are carried subject to personalized inspection. In case the Booking Customer is absent at the time of pick up for the inspection of fragile Luggage item, then the inspection will be done in the presence of the person as authorized by the Booking Customer. Inspection before carriage is compulsory and the fragile item will not be picked up if the case is locked or unavailable for checking. Packing will be completed once the item is inspected before it is sealed. The item shall be further stored in a separate case to ensure safety during transit.<br/>
• Maximum weight per Luggage is restricted to 40Kilograms for all categories other than fragile Luggage item. The maximum height is restricted to 40inches.<br/>
• The Sealed Luggage bag will not be opened and/or searched by our personnel without your consent except where we are required to do so by any regulatory or governmental authority or the airport personnel.<br/>
• We also ensure the Luggage before we cover each piece we carry. Insurance will be applied to all the Luggage counts. Insurance amount and its taxes are non-refundable for cancellations made on the date of service or otherwise. Insurance once purchased is non-refundable and non-transferable.<br/>
• You are strongly advised against packing valuable and fragile items in your Luggage.In the event that you have selected the “Food and beverage” option on our Website/Mobile App then your Luggage can only contain food and beverage. Items that are leak-proof will be taken to be carted. Some items of value are listed below to strongly indicate the contents that are not covered under Insurance or Travel Cloth’s liability including but not limited to:<br/>
<br/>o Laptops
<br/>o Portable electronics
<br/>o Any item that could be damaged or broken during transit
<br/>o Medication
<br/>o Securities / negotiable papers
<br/>o Silverware / precious metals / precious stones
<br/>o Money / jewelry / other valuable items
<br/>o Business / travel / identification documents
<br/>o Any illegal substances or items of explosive nature
<br/>o Items which are not leak proof
